article.headline: Lamar 71, Texas-San Antonio 59
article.story: SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- James Davis was 6-of-8 from the field for 15 points in Lamar's 71-59 win against Texas-San Antonio on Saturday night. Matthew Barrow added 14 points, including three 3-pointers, and Darren Hopkins had 13 points and eight rebounds. Lawrence Nwevo came off the bench to score 10 points and grab eight rebounds. The Cardinals (7-8) led 27-20 at halftime and built a 15-point lead with 2:56 remaining in the game. They never trailed. Andrew Francis came off the bench to lead the Roadrunners (4-10) with 14 points and eight rebounds. He hit 6-of-9 from the free-throw line. Isaiah Allen added 11 points.
